## 1. Purpose and Scope

### 1.1 Purpose

This Standard Operating Procedure (SOP) establishes a structured, auditable, and ethically grounded framework for the responsible development, deployment, operation, and retirement of Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) systems within the organization's global technology environment. It ensures that AI use aligns with applicable regulatory requirements, internal quality standards, and internationally recognized responsible AI principles.

This SOP applies to all AI/ML technologies—including generative AI, predictive analytics, automation systems, and AI-assisted decision-making tools—operating in or interfacing with GxP-regulated environments (e.g., systems supporting drug development, clinical trials, manufacturing, and quality assurance), as well as non-regulated but business-critical IT infrastructure.

### 1.2 Scope

This SOP applies to:

| Scope Element | Inclusions |
|---|---|
| **Systems Covered** | AI/ML models, large language models (LLMs), robotic process automation with AI components, AI-assisted monitoring and analytics tools |
| **Environments Covered** | GxP-regulated systems, cloud-hosted platforms, hybrid infrastructure, and internal enterprise applications |
| **Personnel Covered** | AI developers, data scientists, cloud engineers, system administrators, technology leads, risk/compliance officers, and third-party AI vendors |
| **Geographic Applicability** | All global technology sites and remote teams operating under the organization's IT governance |

### 1.3 Exclusions

This SOP does not cover:

- Purely manual statistical analysis performed without AI/ML tooling
- Third-party validated software used without modification, governed under separate vendor qualification SOPs
- Non-technology business processes that do not involve automated AI decision-making

