## 8. Training, Awareness, and Continuous Improvement

### 8.1 Mandatory Training Requirements

All personnel within scope of this SOP must complete the following training:

| Training Module | Target Audience | Frequency | Delivery Method |
|---|---|---|---|
| Responsible AI Principles and Policy Overview | All in-scope personnel | At onboarding + annually | E-learning (LMS) |
| AI Risk Classification and Governance Process | AI Developers, Technology Leads, Risk Officers | At onboarding + annually | Instructor-led or virtual workshop |
| GxP Requirements for AI/ML Systems | AI Developers, Cloud Engineers, System Admins | At onboarding + upon regulatory updates | Blended learning |
| AI Incident Response Procedures | All in-scope personnel | Annually + after P1/P2 events | Tabletop exercise + e-learning |
| Data Privacy in AI Systems (GDPR/HIPAA) | AI Developers, Data Scientists, Cloud Engineers | Annually | E-learning (LMS) |
| AI Security: Prompt Injection, Model Security | AI Developers, Cloud Engineers | Annually | Technical workshop |
| AI Vendor Assessment and Third-Party Risk | Risk/Compliance Officers, Procurement | Annually | E-learning (LMS) |

### 8.2 Training Records

- All training completions must be recorded in the organization's Learning Management System (LMS)
- Training records constitute GxP-relevant documentation and are subject to audit
- Non-compliance with mandatory training triggers escalation to the employee's manager and HR within 30 days of missed deadline

### 8.3 AI Governance Review Cadence

The following governance activities must occur on a defined schedule:

| Activity | Frequency | Owner | Output |
|---|---|---|---|
| AI Risk Register Review | Quarterly | Risk/Compliance Officer | Updated Risk Register |
| AI System Inventory Audit | Quarterly | Technology Lead | Verified Inventory |
| AI Governance Committee Meeting | Quarterly | Executive Sponsor | Meeting minutes, decisions log |
| SOP Periodic Review | Annually | Risk/Compliance Officer + Technology Lead | Revised SOP or confirmation of currency |
| Regulatory Horizon Scan for AI | Semi-annually | Risk/Compliance Officer | Regulatory Impact Assessment |
| AI Ethics Review | Annually | AI Governance Committee | Ethics Review Report |

### 8.4 Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)

Performance of the AI governance program must be tracked using the following metrics:

| KPI | Target | Measurement Frequency |
|---|---|---|
| % AI systems with current risk classification in Inventory | 100% | Quarterly |
| % AI systems with validated status prior to production | 100% for Critical/High; 95% for Medium | Quarterly |
| P1/P2 Incident mean time to containment | ≤ 1 hour (P1); ≤ 4 hours (P2) | Per incident |
| CAPA closure rate within due date | ≥ 90% | Quarterly |
| Mandatory training completion rate | ≥ 95% | Monthly |
| AI vendor assessments completed prior to procurement | 100% | Quarterly |
| Periodic AI system reviews completed on schedule | ≥ 95% | Semi-annually |

### 8.5 Continuous Improvement Process

This SOP and the broader AI governance framework must be treated as living documents subject to continuous improvement through:

1. **Lessons Learned Reviews** — Conducted after each P1/P2 incident or significant model failure
2. **Regulatory Change Management** — Triggered updates when applicable laws (EU AI Act, FDA guidance) are revised or new guidance issued
3. **Technology Watch** — Semi-annual scan of emerging AI risks, tools, and best practices to inform framework updates
4. **Stakeholder Feedback** — Annual survey of in-scope teams to identify governance friction points and improvement opportunities
5. **Benchmarking** — Participation in industry working groups (e.g., PhUSE, DIA, ISPE) to align with Life Sciences AI best practices

